---
description: Keep mobile IAP and Stripe shop flows strictly separate
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

This project has separate payment responsibilities.

Payment separation:
- mobile in-app coin purchases -> platform IAP only
- shop or web checkout -> Stripe only

Strictly forbidden:
- do not mix IAP and Stripe in the same purchase flow
- do not send in-app coin purchase buttons to Stripe
- do not send shop/web checkout through mobile IAP
- do not reuse one payment handler for both systems unless the separation is explicit and safe
- do not create confusing fallbacks from IAP to Stripe inside the app
- do not fake successful purchases across systems

Implementation rules:
- preserve existing UI
- wire each visible payment button to the correct payment backend
- keep product identifiers and checkout identifiers separate
- keep success, failure, and cancel states separate
- keep entitlement/coin-credit logic grounded in the real payment source
- do not duplicate credits from both systems

Default behavior:
IAP and Stripe must remain separate and clearly scoped.
